- if current_user.tips_shown
  #gs_container.js_tips_container
    #getting_started_title
      %h2= "Getting started with #{yield(:title)}"
      = render :partial => 'shared/tips_hide'
    .getting_started
      .message
        %p Use Projects for the high-level health programmes that your organization implements. A project is generally defined as a contractual agreement with a funder or oversight body to support health goals in the country.
        %ul.bulleted
          %li Add a new project for each programme/project you have, or use the bulk csv upload.
          %li Select the location(s) that the project takes place in.
          %li Show where the funding came from (you can have multiple funding sources)
          %li Indicate the Past Expenditure and/or Current Budget for the entire project
          %li
            Add
            = link_to "Activities", new_response_activity_path(@response)
            for each Project
          %li If the project is implemented by multiple entities/partners, add these to the relevant Activities.
        %p
          There is great
          = link_to "online help", help_link, :target => "_blank"
          in HRT and you can always
          = link_to "contact the Support Team", contact_link, :target => "_blank"
          at anytime to ask us a question.
